article.description: — Clay Gayman tied his career high with a season-high 21 points as Abilene Christian stretched its winning streak to seven games, routing Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 83-55 on Saturday.
article.headline: Gayman lifts Abilene Christian past Texas A&M-CC 83-55
article.linkText: Gayman lifts Abilene Christian past Texas A&M-CC 83-55
article.story: ABILENE, Texas -- — Clay Gayman tied his career high with a season-high 21 points as Abilene Christian stretched its winning streak to seven games, routing Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 83-55 on Saturday. Kolton Kohl had 16 points for Abilene Christian (18-3, 10-1 Southland Conference). Coryon Mason added 10 points. Nolan Bertain had 16 points for the Islanders (3-15, 0-9), who have now lost nine consecutive games. De’Lazarus Keys added 15 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
